          "author": {
            "login": "ConcaveTrillion"
          },
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #31\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#324\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `Makefile:234`\n- `Makefile:240`\n- `Makefile:257`\n- `Makefile:263`\n\n`HF_LAYOUT_UPSTREAM`, `HF_LAYOUT_FORK`, `HF_LAYOUT_MIRROR`, and `SHA` are interpolated into shell recipes.\n\nImpact:\n\n- If untrusted Make variables are supplied, developer-only targets can be command-injection surfaces.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Validate variables with strict regexes, or move logic into Python using subprocess argument lists.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closedAt": "2026-05-22T16:34:45Z",
