          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #31\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    Developer layout-fork targets interpolate Make variables into shell recipes.\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    If untrusted Make variables are supplied, developer-only targets can become command-injection surfaces.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `Makefile:234`\n- `Makefile:240`\n- `Makefile:257`\n- `Makefile:263`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Validate variables with strict regexes, or move logic into Python using subprocess argument lists.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
